                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d605">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 868.001 G 29/4.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Athens</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-03-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Queen received the President’s message of condolence just before she left for
                    Saloniki. It was the first message to arrive from any foreign country and has
                    been published conspicuously by the afternoon newspapers.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Schurman</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
